==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bull trout
<hw>Bull" trout`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>In England, a large salmon trout of several species, as <spn>Salmo
trutta</spn> and <spn>Salmo Cambricus</spn>, which ascend rivers; --
called also <altname>sea trout</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def><spn>Salvelinus malma</spn> of California and Oregon; -- called
also <altname>Dolly Varden trout</altname> and <altname>red-spotted
trout</altname>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The huso or salmon of the
Danube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bullweed</ent>⟦br⟧
